Week 5 - BBO Capstone Project

Discussion of Week 4's Strategy and Modifications for Week 5, based on Week 4 Query Outcomes:


For Function 1, Week 4's strategy (Matern kernel with nu=1.5 - because Function 1 is spiky - with applied Automatic Relevance Determination (ARD) with aggresive 
baseline and wider bounds, Sobol sampling and Thompson Sampling - which is Week 3's Strategy repeated for Week 4) has yielded a very poor outcome 
(-6.136546579871625e-92). This is actually the lowest output value ever within the existing dataset for this function so far. This result is quite surprising, 
as previously, Week 3's predicted query following the same startegy, yielded a pretty high and quite satisfactory output (4.363936459722764e-23, the second highest 
output within Function 1's dataset) in terms of the strategy's direction. This week's very different output, despite following the same query prediction startegy 
as last week, points towards the fact that the Gaussian Process for this function is very high variance at this moment, because Thompson sampling is inherently 
stochastic. 

For Week 5, a sligthly modified version of Week 3's and Week 4's strategy, where the EI acqusition function will be employed instead, using a high exploration 
coefficient (xi = 0.1), as this acquisition function has not yet been tested for Function 1 and might work very well. Also, a WhiteKernel will be used instead of 
manually setting the alpha noise parameter for the kernel, as the alpha =1e-4 used so far is actually assuming that the noise is higher (std = 0.01) than the true std shows 
at this stage (std = 0.000929). The WhiteKernel parameters are set based on computed std. dev. of the up-to-date dataset (0.000929). Z formula will also be 
improved to account for post_std = 0, which would cause Z = NaN and lead to numerical instability further down the line, causing unwanted meaningless query 
prediction (this has not been implemented so far, but will be from now on, because it is a safer strategy that prevents meaningless query predictions and waste 
valuable resources). Therefore, for Function 1, the strategy for Week 5 will be: Matern kernel with nu=1.5 - because Function 1 is spiky - and WhiteKernel to 
automatically simulate and learn the noise from existing data, with applied Automatic Relevance Determination (ARD) with aggresive baseline - 
length_scale=[0.1]*2 - and wider length_scale_bounds=(1e-6, 1e8), WhiteKernel(noise_level=1e-6, noise_level_bounds=(1e-16, 1e-2)), Sobol sampling and EI acqusition 
function will be employed with a high exploration coefficient (xi = 0.1). 

